k with native AI integration\n- Launched Cursor 2.0 in late 2025 with proprietary Composer model\n- ~4x faster generation speed, completing most interactions in 30 seconds\n- Pricing: ~$20/month Pro version\n- Strong in multi-file editing and project-level understanding\n\n**2. Windsurf (Codeium)**\n- Formerly Codeium's IDE, positions itself as \"AI and Developer as Co-Authors\"\n- Key differentiator: Remote indexing for large codebases (1M+ lines)\n- Pricing: ~$15/month Pro version (slightly cheaper than Cursor)\n- Features \"Super Complete\" mode to compete with Cursor\n- Focus on cloud-based indexing to reduce local resource usage\n\n**3. Other Notable Tools:**\n- **Claude Code**: Terminal-based AI coding tool (not an IDE)\n- **Trae**: Free option with Claude integration, popular in China\n- **Zed**: Another AI-native editor in the space\n\n### The Competitive Landscape:\nThe search results suggest the AI IDE market is dominated by Cursor and Windsurf, with ongoing \"wars\" between these platforms. However, I did not find any concrete information about a new AI IDE competitor that specifically launched in February 2025.\n\n**Would you like me to:**\n1. Search with different keywords to find this specific February 2025 launch?\n2. Look for more recent AI IDE announcements?\n3. Search for startup funding or product releases in the AI coding space around that timeframe?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
