tures**:\n  - File system-based hierarchical memory architecture\n  - Multi-modal memory storage (conversations, documents, images)\n  - Cross-session association capabilities\n  - RAG and LLM dual-mode retrieval\n  - Supports multiple model providers (OpenRouter, etc.)\n  - Achieved 92.09% reasoning accuracy in Locomo benchmark tests\n  - Designed for 24/7 proactive agents\n\n### 2. **Agent Skills for Context Engineering**\n- **GitHub**: [muratcankoylan/Agent-Skills-for-Context-Engineering](https://github.com/muratcankoylan/Agent-Skills-for-Context-Engineering)\n- **Language**: Python (100%)\n- **Popularity**: 8.6k stars, 687 forks\n- **Cited by**: Peking University AI Laboratory\n- **Focus**: Solving context window management and multi-agent collaboration problems\n- **Features**: Context fundamentals, multi-agent architecture, memory systems, \"progressive disclosure\" design philosophy\n\n### 3. **OpenClaw Memory System**\n- **Architecture**: File-based memory (Markdown + logs) stored on disk\n- **Structure**:\n  - `~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md` (strategic long-term memory)\n  - `memory/` directory with daily logs (e.g., `2026-02-20.md`)\n  - Conversation sessions and history\n  - Optional plugins for semantic/long-term memory\n- **Use**: Per-project sessions with history\n\n### 4. **PicoClaw**\n- **Release Date**: February 9, 2026\n- **Features**: \n  - Runs on $10 hardware with <10MB RAM\n  - Workspace structure including sessions/, memory/ (MEMORY.md), cron/, skills/\n  - 99% less memory usage than traditional agents\n\n## **2026 Agentic AI Trends - Memory & Context**\n\nAccording to multiple sources, **2026 is seeing major breakthroughs in AI agent memory and long-term context capabilities**:\n\n### Key Developments:\n1. **Context Window Expansion**: From thousands of tokens to tens of thousands of tokens\n2. **Long-term Autonomy**: Agents can now work for weeks without losing context or deviating from goals\n3. **10x Model Context Processing Improvement**: Supporting complete software project development and cross-departmental business processes\n4. **Three-tier Memory Architecture**:\n   - **Short-term memory enhancement**: Context window expansion\n   - **Long-term memory architecture**: Systems like \"Memory Bear\" building human-like memory architectures with multi-modal information perception\n   - **Self-evolution capability**: Agents that optimize decision models through reinforcement learning and user feedback\n\nThe search results indicate that February 2026 is a pivotal time for AI agent memory systems, with multiple production-ready frameworks emerging and significant improvements in long-term context retention capabilities.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
