      "I found several relevant results about AI agent CI/CD deployment orchestration and DevOps workflows, with specific events and resources scheduled for February 2026. Here's what I discovered:\n\n## **Key February 2026 Events & Resources:**\n\n### **Microsoft Reactor Agentic DevOps Series**\n- **February 18, 2026**: \"Modernize your Java apps in days with AI Agents\" - Learn how to analyze, upgrade, and migrate Java apps to cloud using autonomous AI agents in GitHub Copilot\n- **February 25, 2026**: \"AI-powered workflows with GitHub and Azure DevOps\" - Covering hybrid adoption, integration best practices, and agent-based automation for DevOps\n\n### **Microsoft Reactor Hackathon (February 10 - March 15, 2026)**\nFeatures a **\"Best solution leveraging agentic DevOps to automate CI/CD, incident response, and reliability engineering\"** category with a **\"Best Multi-Agent System\"** prize for sophisticated multi-agent orchestration using Microsoft Agent Framework and A2A protocols.\n\n### **Recent GitHub Blog Post (February 13, 2026)**\n\"Automate repository tasks with GitHub Agentic Workflows\" - Shows practical examples of continuous AI working with CI/CD practices, including daily automated reporting workflows.\n\n## **Industry Trends for 2026:**\n\n### **From \"Generation\" to \"Orchestration\"**\n2026 is being called the **\"Delivery Phase\"** for AI, with a major shift from:\n- Content generation → Workflow orchestration\n- Chat capabilities → Task execution\n- Model parameter competition → Cost, governance, and organizational capability competition\n\n### **Multi-Agent Systems Becoming Standard**\nOrganizations are adopting specialized agents:\n- **Planning agents** - Decompose tasks\n- **Coding agents** - Write code\n- **Testing agents** - Verify quality\n- **Operations agents** - Handle deployment and monitoring\n\n### **agents24 Multi-Agent Orchestration System**\nA comprehensive DevOps solution featuring:\n- **91 specialized AI agents**\n- **15 workflow coordinators**\n- **47 agent skills**\n- **65 focused plugins**\n\nComplete pipeline capabilities including:\n- Automated code review\n- Security vulnerability scanning\n- Dependency auditing\n- Unit/integration/E2E testing\n- Kubernetes operations with GitOps workflows (ArgoCD/Flux)\n- Progressive delivery strategies\n\n## **Key Benefits of AI Agent DevOps:**\n- **Speed**: Deployment time reduced from days to minutes\n- **Security**: Standardized blueprints ensure tested patterns\n- **Intelligence**: Context-aware configuration decisions within governance guardrails\n\nThe search results show that February 2026 is an active month for AI agent DevOps, with Microsoft leading educational initiatives and the industry moving toward production-ready multi-agent orchestration systems."
