thropic/claude-code`)\n- **Key Features**: \n  - Cross-platform compatibility (desktop, CLI, IDE plugins)\n  - 1 million token context window (with Opus 4.6)\n  - Multi-file editing and codebase-wide refactoring\n  - Pricing: $17/month (Pro), $100/month (Max), custom enterprise pricing\n\n### **2. GitHub Copilot Workspace (Microsoft)**\n- **VS Code**: Deep integration with full project generation\n- **JetBrains**: Official plugin for IntelliJ-based IDEs\n- **Neovim**: Via copilot.vim community plugin\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Multi-agent collaboration\n  - 100万 token上下文\n  - GitHub integration\n  - Subscription: $10/month (individual), enterprise pricing available\n\n### **3. JetBrains AI Assistant**\n- **JetBrains**: Native integration across entire JetBrains family\n- **Core Capabilities**:\n  - Code refactoring, debugging, documentation generation\n  - Seamless integration with IDE functionality\n  - Best for Java, Kotlin, Python developers\n  - Version: 253.30387.147 (February 2026)\n\n### **4. Cursor (AI-Native IDE)**\n- **VS Code**: Based on VS Code kernel, full plugin compatibility\n- **Supports**: Claude Opus 4.6, Sonnet 4.6, and other models\n- **Key Features**:\n  - Natural language to code conversion\n  - Multi-file editing (Composer mode)\n  - Cross-file refactoring\n  - Pricing: $20/month (Pro), 2-week free trial\n\n### **5. Cline - Open Source Alternative**\n- **Platforms**: VS Code, JetBrains (IntelliJ IDEA, PyCharm, etc.)\n- **Supports**: Claude, GPT, Gemini, DeepSeek models\n- **Pricing**: Completely free and open source\n- **Best for**: Cross-platform developers wanting multi-model support\n\n### **6. Other Notable Tools**\n\n**Tabnine**:\n- VS Code, JetBrains, Neovim support\n- Local/cloud dual mode\n- Privacy-focused\n- Free basic tier available\n\n**Amazon Q Developer (CodeWhisperer)**:\n- VS Code extension via AWS Toolkit\n- JetBrains plugin available\n- Free individual tier\n- Best for AWS/cloud development\n\n**Codeium**:\n- Completely free AI code assistant\n- VS Code, JetBrains, Neovim support\n- 40+ programming languages\n- Permanent free tier\n\n## 📊 **February 2026 Model Landscape**\n\n| Model | Context Window | Best For | API Cost |\n|-------|---------------|----------|----------|\n| **Claude Opus 4.6** | 200K-1M | Complex refactoring | $15/$75 per 1M tokens |\n| **GPT-5.3-Codex** | 128K | Algorithm optimization | $10/$30 per 1M tokens |\n| **Gemini 3.1 Pro** | 2M+ | Ultra-large projects | $3.50/$10.50 per 1M tokens |\n| **DeepSeek V4** | 128K | Cost-effective daily coding | $0.14/$0.28 per 1M tokens |\n| **Claude Sonnet 4.6** | 200K | Daily coding (best balance) | $3/$15 per 1M tokens |\n\n## 💡 **Key Insights for February 2026**\n\n1. **Agentic AI Revolution**: Tools have evolved from simple code completion to autonomous agents that can handle multi-file refactoring and complex architectural changes\n\n2. **Cross-Environment Integration**: Leading tools like Claude Code now work seamlessly across web, desktop, CLI, and IDE environments\n\n3. **Long Context Standard**: Most major tools now support 100K+ token contexts, enabling understanding of entire codebases\n\n4. **Pricing Shifts**: DeepSeek offers the most cost-effective solution ($0.14/M input tokens), while premium tools like Claude Opus 4.6 command higher prices for complex tasks\n\n5. **IDE Native Integration**: JetBrains AI Assistant and GitHub Copilot have the deepest IDE integration, while Claude Code offers the most flexible cross-platform approach\n\nThe search results show that as of February 2026, the AI coding tools market has matured significantly with strong competition, improved capabilities, and diverse pricing options for different use cases.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
